Summary: Multi-planet systems (MPSes) provide insight into planet composition and formation. We propose to expand the sample size of MPSes by collecting TESS 2-min or 20-sec cadence observations of 1944 stars hosting at least one planet or candidate. We expect to detect dozens of previously undetected planets with this effort.
